full_text:
Hi Rita,

Welcome to the group.  Yes, Bruce is correct... my sound chamber design is an experiment to see how well that design works.  I took the basic components of a typical ghost box system and placed them into the plastic enclosure. But to hear what is desired does not always require a chamber. The chamber is just a place where the three sound components can mix and be captured by the microphone.
Just one of many different methods that can be used.

I have even got good results by just using a 12-470 and a recorder in the open air.

I did build a couple of new chamber systems and will probably build one more for a total of 4.  And I&#39;ll probably provide some of those to some locals here to test. I&#39;d like to get others input on this experimental design. LC is also putting one together using the 12-469. So we will have data from that area too.

Again... welcome to the group.

- Mike

